gomodel:SYNGO_4515  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Long-term depression (LTD) at parallel fiber-Purkinje cell synapses is enhanced in delphilin KO mice. Ca2+ influx through voltage-gated Ca2+ channels, mGluR1 activation and AMPA receptor activation are required to induce LTD.\nWhen the calcium buffer EGTA (10 mM) was introduced into a Purkinje cell, LTD was strongly suppressed in the wild-type mice but only weakly in the mutant mice (Fig. 4B). These results suggest that LTD was induced with less intracellular Ca2+\nin the mutant mice.\nThis ticket is related to ticket ID 4511.. Experimental description: LTD induction was facilitated at PF-PC synapses in Delphilin mutant mice (page 1, e2297). And: ...backcrossed 5 times to theC57BL/6 strain," ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9377-7414" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0269-0311" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9681-3318" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-9880-1214" ;
        dc:date           "2021-01-28" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_4515" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

